                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1311</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1917, noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On both sides border between Camaguey and Oriente Provinces, 400 miles east of
                    Habana, numerous leaderless bands, mostly negroes, operating, robbing country,
                    stores and houses. Colonel Varona capable organizer and officer recently placed
                    in command of that district with adequate forces and I hope for early
                    suppression of bandits.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
